<br />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.un.org/en/ga/president/73/ President of the 73rd General Assembly]\n* [https://www.un.org/en/ga/73/agenda/index.shtml Agenda for the 73rd General Assembly]\n\n{{United Nations General Assembly}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n\n[[Category:2018 in the United Nations]]\n[[Category:2019 in the United Nations]]\n[[Category:Sessions of the United Nations General Assembly]]\n[[Category:United Nations General Assembly resolutions]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox summit meeting\n| name         = Seventy-third session of the United Nations General Assembly\n| other_titles = \n| logo         = \n| logo_alt     = \n| image        = Reuni\u00f3n con AFESE (38623712645) (cropped).jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = President of the 73rd General Assembly <br> [[Mar\u00eda Fernanda Espinosa|Mar\u00eda Fernanda Espinosa Garc\u00e9s]]\n| country      = {{flag|United Nations}}\n| date         = 18 September 2018 \u2013 17 September 2019\n| motto        =\n| venues       = [[United Nations Headquarters]]\n| cities       = [[New York City]]\n| participants = [[Member states of the United Nations|Member States of the United Nations]]\n| chairperson  = \n| follows      = [[Seventy-second session of the United Nations General Assembly|72nd]]\n| precedes     = [[Seventy-fourth session of the United Nations General Assembly|74th]]\n| website      = [http://www.un.org/en/ga/ www.un.org/en/ga/]\n| keypoints    =\n| compactnav   = yes\n}}\n\nThe '''Seventy-third session of the United Nations General Assembly''' was opened on 18 September 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2018/09/1019712|title=Bring the United Nations closer to the people, urges Assembly President in her inaugural speech|last=|first=|date=18 September 2018|work=UN News|access-date=22 September 2018}}</ref> The [[President of the United Nations General Assembly|President of]] the [[United Nations General Assembly]] is from the [[GRULAC]] group.\n\n==Organisation for the session==\n=== President ===\nEcuadorian Foreign Minister, [[Mar\u00eda Fernanda Espinosa|Mar\u00eda Fernanda Espinosa Garc\u00e9s]] was elected as President of the General Assembly on 5 June 2018. <ref name=\"Annual Report 18\">{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=United Nations Handbook 2018\u201319 |url=https://www.mfat.govt.nz/assets/Handbooks/UN-Handbook-2018-19-pdf.pdf |edition= 56th |location=Wellington |page=22 |publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade of New Zealand |date=2018 |issn= 0110-1951}}</ref>\n\n=== Vice-Presidents ===\nThere will be twenty-one Vice-Presidents for the 73rd Session. They will be: <ref name=\"Annual Report 18\"></ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=http://www.un.org/en/ga/73/pdf/delegates_handbook_73rd_session_en.pdf|title=Delegates' Handbook, Seventy-third Session of the United Nations General Assembly|last=|first=|publisher=United Nations|year=2018|isbn=|location=New York|pages=}}</ref>\n\nThe five [[Permanent members of the United Nations Security Council|permanent members of the Security Council]]:\n* {{flag| China}}\n* {{flag| France}}\n* {{flag| Russian Federation}}\n* {{flagdeco| United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland]]\n* {{flagdeco| United States}} [[United states of america|United States of America]]\nAs well as the following nations:\n* {{flag|Algeria}}\n* {{flag|Burkina Faso}}\n* {{flag|Cambodia}}\n* {{flag|Cyprus}}\n* {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}}\n* {{flagdeco|Gambia}} [[Gambia|Gambia (Republic of The)]]\n* {{flag|Guyana}}\n* {{flag|Iraq}}\n* {{flag|Japan}}\n* {{flag|Namibia}}\n* {{flag|Panama}}\n* {{flag|Qatar}}\n* {{flag|San Marino}}\n* {{flag|Spain}}\n* {{flag|Sudan}}\n* {{flag|Ukraine}}\n\n=== Committees ===\nThe following were elected as Chairs and officers of the General Assembly committees for the 73rd Session: <ref name=\"Annual Report 18\"></ref>\n\n[[United Nations General Assembly First Committee|'''First Committee '''(Disarmament and International Security)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n| [[Ion Jinga|H.E. Mr. Ion Jinga]] || {{flag| Romania}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Ms. Marissa Edwards || {{flag| Guyana}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. No\u00ebl Diarra || {{flag| Mali}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Jos\u00e9 Ata\u00edde Amaral || {{flag| Portugal}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Muna Zawani Md Idris || {{flag|Brunei Darussalam}} || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n[[United Nations General Assembly Second Committee|'''Second Committee '''(Economic and Financial)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n|  H.E. Mr. Jorge Skinner-Kle\u00e9 Arenales  || {{flag|Guatemala}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Mr. Mehdi Remaoun || {{flag|Algeria}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Hessa Muneer Mohammed Rashed AlAteibi || {{flag|United Arab Emirates}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Cedric Braquetti  || {{flag| Monaco}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Anneli Lepp || {{flag|Estonia}} || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n[[United Nations General Assembly Third Committee|'''Third Committee '''(Social, Humanitarian and Cultural)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n| [[Mahmoud Saikal|H.E. Mr. Mahmoud Saikal]] || {{flag| Afghanistan}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Ms. Lahya Itedhimbwa Shikongo || {{flag| Namibia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Martin Kov\u00e1\u010dik || {{flag| Slovakia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Andr\u00e9s Molina Linares || {{flag| Guatemala}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Katharina Konzett-Stoffl || {{flag| Austria}} || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n[[United Nations General Assembly Fourth Committee|'''Fourth Committee '''(Special Political and Decolonization)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n| H.E. Mr. Lewis Garseedah Brown II  || {{flag| Liberia}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Mr. Faisal Nasser M. Alhakbani || {{flag| Saudi Arabia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. D\u00e1niel Goldea || {{flag| Hungary}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Michael O\u2019Toole || {{flag| Ireland}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Luis Mauricio Arancibia Fern\u00e1ndez || {{flagdeco| Bolivia}} [[Bolivia|Bolivia (Plurinational State of)]] || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n[[United Nations General Assembly Fifth Committee|'''Fifth Committee '''(Administrative and Budgetary)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n| [[Gillian Bird|H.E. Ms. GiIlian Bird]] || {{flag| Australia}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Mr. Fabio Esteban Pedraza-Torres || {{flag| Colombia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Andre Lipand || {{flag| Estonia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Haseeb Gohar || {{flag| Pakistan}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Hicham Oussihamou || {{flag| Morocco}} || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n[[United Nations General Assembly Sixth  Committee|'''Sixth Committee''' (Legal)]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n! Name\n! Country\n! Position\n|-\n| H.E. Mr. Michel Xavier Biang  || {{flag| Gabon}} || Chairperson\n|- \n| Ms. Maria Angela Ponce || {{flag| Philippines}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Barbara Krem\u017ear || {{flag| Slovenia}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Mr. Patrick Luna || {{flag| Brazil}} || Vice-Chair\n|- \n| Ms. Nadia Alexandra Kalb || {{flag| Austria}} || Rapporteur\n|- \n|}\n\n=== Seat Allocation ===\nAs is tradition during each session of the [[General Assembly]], Secretary-General [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]] will draw lots to see which member state would take the helm at the first seat in the General Assembly Chamber, with the other member states following according to the English translation of their name, the same order would be followed in the six main committees.<ref name=\"data\">{{cite web|url=http://www.unhcr.org/5028f5129.pdf |format=PDF |title=63rd Session of the Executive Committee of the High Commissioner's Programme, Geneva, 1 - 5 October 2012 |publisher=Unhcr.org |accessdate=2 October 2015}}</ref> For this session, Mali was chosen to take the first seat of the General Assembly Chamber.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== General Debate ===\n{{main article|General Debate of the seventy-third session of the United Nations General Assembly}}\nMost states will have a representative speaking about issues concerning their country and the hopes for the coming year as to what the UNGA will do. This is an opportunity for the member states to opine on international issues of their concern. The General Debate will occur from 25 September to 1 October 2018, with the exception of the intervening Sunday.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2018/09/1019842|title=6 things to know about the General Assembly as UN heads into high level week|last=|first=|date=18 September 2018|work=UN News|access-date=22 September 2018}}</ref> The theme for this year's debate was chosen by [[President of the United Nations General Assembly|President]] [[Mar\u00eda Fernanda Espinosa]] as \u201cMaking the United Nations relevant to all people: Global leadership and shared responsibilities for peaceful, equitable and sustainable societies\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.un.org/pga/72/wp-content/uploads/sites/51/2018/07/PGA-letter_-UNGA73-theme-1.pdf|title=Letter of the President-elect of the 73rd Session of the United Nations General Assembly to Heads of States|date=26 July 2018|access-date=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe order of speakers is given first to member states, then observer states and supranational bodies. Any other observers entities will have a chance to speak at the end of the debate, if they so choose. Speakers will be put on the list in the order of their request, with special consideration for ministers and other government officials of similar or higher rank. According to the rules in place for the General Debate, the statements should be in one of the United Nations official languages of [[Arabic]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]], [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[Russian language|Russian]] or [[Spanish language|Spanish]], and will be translated by the [[United Nations translators]]. Each speaker is requested to provide 20 advance copies of their statements to the conference officers to facilitate translation and to be presented at the podium. Speeches are requested to be limited to five minutes, with seven minutes for supranational bodies.<ref name=\"data\"/>\n\nForeign ministers and high representatives participating in the General Debate signed the Code of Conduct Towards Achieving a World Free of Terrorism. The Code of Conduct was the brainchild of Kazakhstan's President Nursultan Nazarbayev. The main goal of the document is implementation of a wide range of international commitments to counter terrorism and establishing a broad global coalition towards achieving a world free of terrorism by 2045.<ref>{{cite web |title=At UN General Assembly, FM presents Kazakh initiatives, meets foreign officials, US business representatives |url=https://astanatimes.com/2018/10/at-un-general-assembly-fm-presents-kazakh-initiatives-meets-foreign-officials-us-business-representatives/ |website=astanatimes.com}}</ref>\n<!--==Agenda==\n===Issues===-->\n\n==Resolutions==\n{{Outdated as of | year = 2018 | month = 12 | day = 3 }}\n\nThe following are resolutions the General Assembly has passed in its 73rd session, {{As of|2018|12|3|lc=y}}. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.un.org/en/ga/73/resolutions.shtml |title=Resolutions of the 73rd session |authors=United Nations General Assembly |date=n.d. |website=United Nations General Assembly |publisher=United Nations |access-date= 4 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://research.un.org/en/docs/ga/quick/regular/73 |title=Resolutions adopted by the General Assembly at its 73rd session |authors=Dag Hammarskj\u00f6ld Library |date=n.d. |website=Dag Hammarskj\u00f6ld Library |publisher=United Nations |access-date=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=10% |Resolution\n! width=16% |Date\n! width=10% |Plenary or Committee\n! width=10% |Agenda Item\n! width=10% |Vote \n! width=10% |Passed\n