el}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Mabel (singer) songs]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Steve Mac]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Camille Purcell]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Steve Mac]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mabel (singer)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 single by Mabel}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Boyfriend\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Mabel - Boyfriend.png\n| artist     = [[Mabel (singer)|Mabel]]\n| album      = [[High Expectations]]\n| released   = {{start date|2020|2|26|df=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]<ref name=\"press\"/>\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=46}}\n| label      = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Camille Purcell]]|[[Mabel (singer)|Mabel McVey]]|[[Marlena Shaw]]|Richard Evans|Robert Miller|[[Steve Mac]]}}\n| producer   = Steve Mac\n| chronology = [[Mabel (singer)|Mabel]]\n| prev_title = [[Loneliest Time of Year]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| title      = Boyfriend\n| year       = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|xi3c-9qzrPY|\"Boyfriend\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Boyfriend'''\" is a song by English singer [[Mabel (singer)|Mabel]], released on 26 February 2020. The song is featured as a bonus track on the [[iTunes Store]] edition of Mabel's debut studio album ''[[High Expectations]]'' (2019).<ref>{{Citation|title=High Expectations by Mabel|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/high-expectations/1499357878|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> The song additionally serves as the [[lead single]] from her upcoming second studio album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7907091/sounds-like-a-banger-mabel-teases-new-single-boyfriend|title=Sounds Like A Banger: Mabel Teases New Single &#8220;Boyfriend&#8221;|date=2020-02-25|website=idolator|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> \"Boyfriend\" samples \"[[Remember Me (Blue Boy song)|Remember Me]]\" (1997) by [[Blue Boy (DJ)|Blue Boy]] which in turn sampled \"Woman of the Ghetto\" (1969) by [[Marlena Shaw]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/mabel-new-single-boyfriend-self-empowerment-2615072|title=Mabel delivers powerful message of self empowerment on 'Boyfriend'|date=2020-02-26|website=NME Music News, Reviews, Videos, Galleries, Tickets and Blogs {{!}} NME.COM|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nMabel announced the song's release on 21 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=Mabel|number=1230915120034873349|title=NEW MUSIC LOADINGGGGGG ARE YOU READY?! 26.02 https://Mabel.lnk.to/BoyfriendPreSave ...pic.twitter.com/GO2iaHvtmh|date=21 February 2020|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> She described the song as \"wanting someone in your life doesn't mean you can't still be dat bitchh\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/mabel-releases-new-single-boyfriend-and-explains-its-message-of-self-empowerment__28847/|title=Mabel explains message behind new single Boyfriend|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nMusically, \"Boyfriend\" is an empowering upbeat [[Pop music|pop]] anthem with a bumping production.<ref name=\"UDM\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.udiscovermusic.com/news/mabel-releases-new-single-boyfriend/|title=Mabel Releases Anthemic New Single \"Boyfriend\" {{!}} uDiscover|last=Stavropoulos|first=Laura|date=2020-02-26|website=uDiscover Music|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3157784/mabel-boyfriend-video/|title=Mabel Makes Her '90s Aaliyah Dreams Come True In \"Boyfriend\" Video|last=Roth|first=Madeline|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref name = \"press\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/mabel-releases-brand-new-single-boyfriend/|title=Mabel Releases Brand New Single, \"Boyfriend\"|website=Umusic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> Lyrically, the song sees Mabel wanting a boyfriend, but saying how she doesn't necessarily need one \"I want a boyfriend... Even though a man ain't something I need\".\n\n==Music video==\nThe song's accompanying music video was directed by [[Isaac Rentz]] and was released on 26 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://muumuse.com/2020/02/mabel-boyfriend-video.html/|title=Pick Up the Phone: Mabel Wants a \u2018Boyfriend\u2019|date=2020-02-26|website=MuuMuse|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xi3c-9qzrPY|title=Mabel - Boyfriend (Official Video)|publisher=MabelVEVO|date=Feb 26, 2020|via=YouTube|access-date=28 February 2002}}</ref> According to Mabel the video for \"Boyfriend\" was inspired by late American singer [[Aaliyah]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3157784/mabel-boyfriend-video/|title=Mabel Makes Her '90s Aaliyah Dreams Come True In 'Boyfriend' Video|date=2020-02-26|website=[[MTV News]]|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> It sees Mabel make her ideal boyfriend in an underground computer laboratory.<ref name=\"UDM\" /> It is a gender-reverse flip of the 1985 film ''[[Weird Science (film)|Weird Science]]''.<ref name=\"UDM\" />\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Boyfriend\n| length1 = 3:46\n| headline = Digital download<ref name = \"press\"/>\n}}{{Track listing\n| note1 = [[Ti\u00ebsto]] Remix\n| title1 = Boyfriend\n| length1 = 2:57\n| headline = Digital download - Ti\u00ebsto Remix<ref name = \"Tiesto\"/>\n}}\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/132431788/credits|title=Boyfriend / Mabel|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Mabel (singer)|Mabel]] \u2013 songwriting, vocals\n* [[Steve Mac]] \u2013 [[Record producer|production]], songwriting, keyboard